Agile

Agile is an approach to project management and software development to increase the quality and the reduction into the
time.
Division of big task into smaller tasks and their deployment result into the qualitative approach
It calls for the cross functional and collaborative. Communication and team management are the basic factors int he agile

Chossing an agile
faster deployment
high quality
high team management
cop-up with the outer world
continous collaboration with the teams and clients to deal with the daily changes in the requirements

How the project becomes agile
Organizing and giving the smaller task to each team to deal
Setting of the sprints

Scrum
In scrum a product is built in a serioes of fixed length iterations called sprints
giving the agile teams a framework for shipping software on a regular cadence

